Metadata-Version: 2.1
Name: Driver2Comm
Version: 0.2.0
Summary: A computational framework for associating cancer cell-intrinsic driver genes with -extrinsic cell-cell communication
Home-page: https://github.com/xierunzhi
Author: Runzhi Xie,Junping Li, Yuxuan Hu*, Gao Lin*
Author-email: rzxie1998@gmail.com
Maintainer: Runzhi Xie
Maintainer-email: rzxie1998@gmail.com
License: MIT Licence
Keywords: scRNA-seq,cell-cell communication,cancer driver gene,tumor microenvironment
Platform: any
License-File: LICENSE
Requires-Dist: numpy
Requires-Dist: pandas
Requires-Dist: statsmodels
Requires-Dist: networkx
Requires-Dist: matplotlib
Requires-Dist: scipy

For systematic investigation of the relationship between cancer cell-intrinsic and -extrinsic factors, we develop a general computational framework, Driver2Comm, for associating driver genes of cancer cells with CCC in the TME using single-cell transcriptomics data. 
